---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Service - Cuewise"
  description="Cuewise Terms of Service — short, plain terms for a free, privacy-first new tab extension. No surprises."
>
  <main>

    <!-- 1. Page Hero -->
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="eyebrow">
          <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><path d="M14 2v6h6"/><path d="M16 13H8"/><path d="M16 17H8"/><path d="M10 9H8"/>
          </svg>
          The Fine Print, Kept Simple
        </div>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">Cuewise is free, and your data stays on your own device — so there isn't much to agree to. Here are the plain terms for using it.</p>
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: June 28, 2026</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 2. Terms Cards -->
    <section class="section-pad">
      <div class="wrap">

        <!-- Card 1: Agreement -->
        <div class="content-card glass reveal">
          <h2>
            <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
            </svg>
            The Agreement
          </h2>
          <p>When you install or use the Cuewise extension (the "Service"), you're agreeing to what's on this page. If something here doesn't sit right with you, that's okay — simply don't install or keep using it.</p>
          <p>We've kept this short on purpose. Cuewise is free and your data lives on your device, so there's very little to fence off.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 2: The Service -->
        <div class="content-card glass reveal">
          <h2>
            <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4"/><path d="M12 8h.01"/>
            </svg>
            What Cuewise Is
          </h2>
          <p>Cuewise turns each new tab into a calm dashboard — a hand-picked quote, your focus for the day, reminders, a Pomodoro timer, focus mode, and gentle insights.</p>
          <p>It's free to use, and everything you create stays on your own device. Our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> covers exactly how your data is handled.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 3: Acceptable Use -->
        <div class="content-card glass reveal">
          <h2>
            <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>
            </svg>
            Using It Well
          </h2>
          <p>Cuewise is built for your own focus and calm. Use it lawfully, and please don't:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Disrupt the Service or try to break into the systems behind it</li>
            <li>Reverse-engineer it beyond what its open-source license or the law allows</li>
            <li>Use it to break the law or step on someone else's rights</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 4: Optional Integrations -->
        <div class="content-card glass reveal">
          <h2>
            <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <rect width="18" height="18" x="3" y="4" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="16" x2="16" y1="2" y2="6"/><line x1="8" x2="8" y1="2" y2="6"/><line x1="3" x2="21" y1="10" y2="10"/>
            </svg>
            Optional Connections
          </h2>
          <p>A few features reach beyond Cuewise, and they only switch on if you turn them on. When they do, the other party's terms apply alongside ours:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Google Calendar:</strong> connect it and Cuewise reads your calendar directly from Google, read-only, to show today's agenda. This follows the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google API Services User Data Policy</a> — details are in the <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>Newsletter:</strong> subscribe and your email is handled as described in the Privacy Policy. Leave anytime.</li>
            <li><strong>Backgrounds &amp; media:</strong> focus-mode imagery and embedded media come from third parties (such as Unsplash and YouTube) under their own terms.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 5: Intellectual Property -->
        <div class="content-card glass reveal">
          <h2>
            <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M12 2l2.4 7.4H22l-6 4.6 2.3 7.4L12 17l-6.3 4.4L8 14 2 9.4h7.6z"/>
            </svg>
            What's Yours, What's Ours
          </h2>
          <p>Everything you create inside the extension — your goals, notes, custom quotes, and settings — is yours, full stop.</p>
          <p>The Cuewise name, logo, and look are ours. The source code is open on <a href={SITE.githubUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a> under the license you'll find in that repository.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 6: Disclaimer -->
        <div class="content-card glass reveal">
          <h2>
            <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" x2="12" y1="9" y2="13"/><line x1="12" x2="12.01" y1="17" y2="17"/>
            </svg>
            Warranty &amp; Liability
          </h2>
          <p>Cuewise comes <strong>"as is"</strong> and <strong>"as available"</strong>, without warranties of any kind, express or implied. We can't promise it will always be available, error-free, or a perfect fit for what you need.</p>
          <p>To the fullest extent the law allows, we're not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages, or for lost data. Since your data lives on your device, do export anything you'd hate to lose.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 7: Changes -->
        <div class="content-card glass reveal">
          <h2>
            <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M11 4H4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-7"/><path d="M18.5 2.5a2.121 2.121 0 0 1 3 3L12 15l-4 1 1-4 9.5-9.5z"/>
            </svg>
            When Things Change
          </h2>
          <p>Cuewise keeps evolving — features may be added, changed, or retired over time, and these terms may shift with them. When they do, we'll update the date at the top of this page. If you keep using Cuewise afterward, that counts as accepting the updated terms.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 9: Contact -->
        <div class="content-card glass reveal">
          <h2>
            <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <rect width="20" height="16" x="2" y="4" rx="2"/><path d="m22 7-8.97 5.7a1.94 1.94 0 0 1-2.06 0L2 7"/>
            </svg>
            Questions?
          </h2>
          <p>If anything here is unclear, we're happy to help:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a></li>
            <li><strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href={SITE.githubIssuesUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open an issue</a></li>
            <li><strong>Support:</strong> <a href="/support/">Visit our support page</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 3. Bottom CTA -->
    <section class="section-pad" style="padding-top:0;">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="final glass reveal">
          <div class="final-inner">
            <h2>That's the Whole Agreement</h2>
            <p>Short, wasn't it? Head back and turn your next tab into a moment of intention.</p>
            <div class="hero-cta">
              <a class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg" href="/">
                <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
                Back to Home
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .content-card h2 svg {
    width: 22px;
    height: 22px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .last-updated {
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
  }
</style>
